"{\"uid\": \"newstatesman.com-culture-sport-2024-07-the-paris-olympics-opening-ceremony-was-more-eurovision-than-bastille-day\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Reviewing politicsand culture since 1913  Rainfall and narrative incoherence marred an ambitious international parade.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 118, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ByNicholas Harris  The supremely frustrating part of visiting any city is transit: the gruelling, hot, bureaucratic business of getting from park to landmark to cathedral.\", \"from\": 120, \"to\": 291, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the most boring and yet fortunately the most forgettable component of any holiday.\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 379, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But, in a baffling turn for an event that is at least partially a tourism advert, it seems the ambition of the Paris Olympics opening ceremony was to try to recreate that experience and serve it up as televisual longform.\", \"from\": 380, \"to\": 601, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The\\u00a0overwhelming mood of the\\u00a0opening ceremony was tedium.\", \"from\": 602, \"to\": 659, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And perhaps its one salvation was that, in its later stages, it featured enough madness to distract from the banality.\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 778, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ahead of yesterday evening's proceedings, the much-touted USP was itsen plein airquality.\", \"from\": 780, \"to\": 869, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That is, instead of being based in a single stadium like every previous opening ceremony, Paris's show would be arranged along a stretch of the River Seine.\", \"from\": 870, \"to\": 1026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 960, \"end\": 965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9654379747492232e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1014, \"end\": 1025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The key objectives were the same as ever: get the Olympic flame to the Olympic cauldron, and parade the competing athletes, all in such a way that keeps 1.5 billion viewers from nodding off.\", \"from\": 1027, \"to\": 1217, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But, this being France, there had to be a metatextual boast of its structural innovation.\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1307, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1234, \"end\": 1240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999958899934, \"rank\": 3.470681353663993e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The story of the ceremony began with a video of the torch arriving incorrectly at an emptystade, before Zinedine Zidane turned up to whisk it off to its true destination.\", \"from\": 1308, \"to\": 1478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1412, \"end\": 1427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zinedine Zidane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He then passed the torch to a mysterious runner: a masked Frenchman in an 18th-century frock coat.\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1578, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And from here it seemed the opening ceremony's premises were set.\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1644, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The flame would be parkoured to its final destination by the lost Assassin's Creed character over rooftop and chimney.\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1763, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1711, \"end\": 1719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Order_of_Assassins\", \"score\": 0.6765142961277042, \"rank\": 0.47816456759722437, \"text\": \"Assassin\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Order_of_Assassins\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Order_of_Assassins\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile the athletes themselves travelled in a fleet of boats downriver (most nations got their own boat, but some had to share).\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1895, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But, for this evening, the Seine was not just any river.\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 1952, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1923, \"end\": 1928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7723553842224774e-31, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Under the command of the French state, it became a miracle of fountains, showering the Olympians as they sailed by.\", \"from\": 1953, \"to\": 2068, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1978, \"end\": 1984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9988095802803378, \"rank\": 0.0011887877534325609, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately for them, however, what was presumably planned as a decorative sprinkle soon became a deluge, as heavy rainfall swamped the city.\", \"from\": 2069, \"to\": 2212, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"National pride briefly swept Britain as images from the sideline showed Keir Starmer in a proper coat, and not one of those awful transparent ponchos.\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2363, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2213, \"end\": 2227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patriotism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National pride\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patriotism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patriotism\"}, {\"begin\": 2242, \"end\": 2249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999871806723, \"rank\": 1.2544732054292375e-08, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 2285, \"end\": 2297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keir_Starmer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keir Starmer\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keir_Starmer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keir_Starmer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, for viewers at home, the camera lenses simply wept and smudged.\", \"from\": 2364, \"to\": 2432, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympians' procession soon dissolved into something far more boring: watching boatfuls of cagouled athletes waving through rainclouds.\", \"from\": 2434, \"to\": 2572, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2434, \"end\": 2447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daptone_Records\", \"score\": 0.9999892659337487, \"rank\": 1.0734181056641533e-05, \"text\": \"The Olympians\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daptone_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daptone_Records\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And it also drew the worst part of opening ceremony coverage out for as long as possible.\", \"from\": 2573, \"to\": 2662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the first barges set off, you could practically hear the creak as our BBC commentators opened their heavy ringbinders of notes and, sounding like lackadaisical sixth formers before a university interview, began to chant national facts as each country sailed by.\", \"from\": 2663, \"to\": 2927, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2736, \"end\": 2739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9999999999936335, \"rank\": 6.43175496537475e-12, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Did you know, for example, that the Cayman Islands used to be called Las Tortugas?\", \"from\": 2928, \"to\": 3010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2964, \"end\": 2978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cayman_Islands\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0406634783161407e-26, \"text\": \"Cayman Islands\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cayman_Islands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cayman_Islands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Or, to quickly hurtle to the other end of alphabet (and the end of the endless procession), that the majority of Tajikistan is 10,000 feet above sea level?\", \"from\": 3011, \"to\": 3166, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3124, \"end\": 3134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajikistan\", \"score\": 0.9999999586771091, \"rank\": 4.127263977137454e-08, \"text\": \"Tajikistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajikistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajikistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Along the way, there were some diversions.\", \"from\": 3168, \"to\": 3210, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There were countless musical and dance acts, including Lady Gaga, a heavy-metal band called Gojira, and excerpts of Bizet and Debussy.\", \"from\": 3211, \"to\": 3345, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3266, \"end\": 3275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}, {\"begin\": 3303, \"end\": 3309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.310475021367428e-44, \"text\": \"Gojira\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\"}, {\"begin\": 3337, \"end\": 3344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claude_Debussy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Debussy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claude_Debussy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claude_Debussy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And as the masked runner made his way westwards, he triggered various cinematic sequences\\u00a0depicting\\u00a0an aspect of French culture.\", \"from\": 3346, \"to\": 3474, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3459, \"end\": 3473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A chorus fromLes Miswas a particular highlight.\", \"from\": 3475, \"to\": 3522, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But others were simply baffling.\", \"from\": 3523, \"to\": 3555, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Why were the Minions fromDespicable Medragged into this?\", \"from\": 3556, \"to\": 3612, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Why were they on a submarine?\", \"from\": 3613, \"to\": 3642, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(A Google search reveals that the original Minions characters - properties of American entertainment giant Comcast via their purchase of NBCUniversal - were created by French animators.)\", \"from\": 3643, \"to\": 3829, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3646, \"end\": 3652, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999307497714903, \"rank\": 6.637167615348892e-05, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 3721, \"end\": 3729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999981182555, \"rank\": 1.6371355960157448e-09, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3750, \"end\": 3757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comcast\", \"score\": 0.9999999972778824, \"rank\": 2.7223235515123625e-09, \"text\": \"Comcast\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comcast\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comcast\"}, {\"begin\": 3811, \"end\": 3817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9988095802803378, \"rank\": 0.0011887877534325609, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Around this point, events made a decided turn towards the bizarre.\", \"from\": 3833, \"to\": 3899, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The story of the runner, and effectively the Olympic torch itself, was abandoned, and attention focused on the gantry-like structure of the Debilly Footbridge, not far from the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 3900, \"to\": 4090, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4040, \"end\": 4058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passerelle_Debilly\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Debilly Footbridge\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passerelle_Debilly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passerelle_Debilly\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On top, what began as a Parisian fashion tribute soon became a general parade of camp and drag, culminating in the moment that a giant cloche was removed from a platter of flowers to reveal a mostly naked Smurf-man (Dionysus, apparently) who delivered a song to camera.\", \"from\": 4091, \"to\": 4360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4307, \"end\": 4315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.993790373488112e-28, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By this point the athletes' boats had all passed through.\", \"from\": 4361, \"to\": 4418, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But a Eurodancing barge had drifted beneath the footbridge, and the ceremony essentially devolved into the most lavish and well-coordinated boat party Paris had ever seen.\", \"from\": 4419, \"to\": 4590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4570, \"end\": 4575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9654379747492232e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From here, it was a wayward clamber back towards being an opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 4592, \"to\": 4667, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Emmanuel Macron and several Olympic grandees made speeches in the (still pouring) rain.\", \"from\": 4668, \"to\": 4755, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4668, \"end\": 4683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And as athletes and Parisians gathered beneath the Eiffel Tower in disciplined formation, it seemed a moment of coherence was upon us.\", \"from\": 4756, \"to\": 4890, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The masked runner was even found; the flame brought before the crowd.\", \"from\": 4891, \"to\": 4960, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But then a further series of very French narrative contrivances: the mysterious identity of the runner became suddenly redundant as he vanished from the story; and the flame was dispatched not towards the Tower, but on another boat back upriver.\", \"from\": 4961, \"to\": 5206, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4995, \"end\": 5001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9988095802803378, \"rank\": 0.0011887877534325609, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Drizzly transit again!\", \"from\": 5207, \"to\": 5229, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Parisians did have some final flourishes in store.\", \"from\": 5231, \"to\": 5285, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"C\\u00e9line Dion delivered a stunning rendition of \\u00c9dith Piaf's \\\"Hymne \\u00e0 l'Amour\\\" from atop the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 5286, \"to\": 5390, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5332, \"end\": 5342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\", \"score\": 0.9999999997962732, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"\\u00c9dith Piaf\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And, after it had retraced the steps of practically the entire ceremony so far, the torch was taken by a group of French athletes through the Louvre, and from there to theJardin des Tuileries.\", \"from\": 5391, \"to\": 5583, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5505, \"end\": 5511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9988095802803378, \"rank\": 0.0011887877534325609, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 5533, \"end\": 5539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 0.9999999992196535, \"rank\": 7.801429225104056e-10, \"text\": \"Louvre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There, they found a cauldron that was affixed to a gorgeous spherical hot air balloon (a genuine French invention), which when lit rose some 30 metres in the air.\", \"from\": 5584, \"to\": 5746, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5681, \"end\": 5687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9988095802803378, \"rank\": 0.0011887877534325609, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will hang above the city for the duration of the Games, casting its glow across the skyline.\", \"from\": 5747, \"to\": 5842, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a moment of rare poignancy in an evening that was otherwise half English bank holiday and half rogue club night.\", \"from\": 5844, \"to\": 5963, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Back in the studio with a boosterish Clare Balding, Rebecca Adlington said that it wasn't her favourite Olympic opening ceremony, even if she admitted it was tarnished by the weather.\", \"from\": 5964, \"to\": 6147, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6001, \"end\": 6014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clare_Balding\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Clare Balding\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clare_Balding\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clare_Balding\"}, {\"begin\": 6016, \"end\": 6033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Adlington\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rebecca Adlington\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Adlington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Adlington\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The event this carnival truly resembled - in its colours, its chaos, and its unyielding but questionable self-confidence - was the Eurovision Song Contest.\", \"from\": 6148, \"to\": 6303, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6279, \"end\": 6302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurovision_Song_Contest\", \"score\": 0.999999999920874, \"rank\": 7.867637412644329e-11, \"text\": \"Eurovision Song Contest\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurovision_Song_Contest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurovision_Song_Contest\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What was really needed\\u00a0therefore was not a different show, but a different commentator - a Norton or a Wogan, someone who could make sense of it all, or at least dryly mock that which they could not.\", \"from\": 6304, \"to\": 6503, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6395, \"end\": 6401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norton_Motorcycle_Company\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.850009124294981e-29, \"text\": \"Norton\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norton_Motorcycle_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norton_Motorcycle_Company\"}, {\"begin\": 6407, \"end\": 6412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wogan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.31675418650268e-21, \"text\": \"Wogan\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wogan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wogan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The temptation, perhaps unfairly, is to compare this to Britain's triumph of 12 years ago.\", \"from\": 6505, \"to\": 6595, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6561, \"end\": 6568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999871806723, \"rank\": 1.2544732054292375e-08, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Danny Boyle's \\\"Isles of Wonder\\\" has become easy to mock in the years since, too readily deployed as a shorthand for a kind of populist-centrist Whiggery.\", \"from\": 6596, \"to\": 6749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6596, \"end\": 6607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danny_Boyle\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Danny Boyle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danny_Boyle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danny_Boyle\"}, {\"begin\": 6740, \"end\": 6748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Whiggism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Whiggery\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Whiggism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Whiggism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But perhaps we needed reminding what these international events can too often be like.\", \"from\": 6750, \"to\": 6836, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In its narrative, pulse and humour, London 2012 is still the opening ceremony to beat.\", \"from\": 6837, \"to\": 6923, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6873, \"end\": 6884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.358176198460303e-14, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Related\", \"from\": 6925, \"to\": 6932, \"entities\": []}]}"